Dlr boosted by Greenspan comments at Europe close . The dollar rose sharply at the European close as dealers took comments by Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan as a hint that U . S . interest rates will be raised to nip inflation in the bud , analysts said . In his semi - annual Humphrey - Hawkins testimony Greenspan said U . S . economic prospects were " quite favourable " but warned of inflation risks and voiced concern about soaring stock prices . " The dollar got a boost because the market took his comments as implying that U . S . rates will go go up soon , " said Michael O ' Hanlon , chief international economist at Paine Webber . 
